                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11651.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-23T15:00:00-07:04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Constitutionalist Chief has requested me verbally to ask if the President
                    will consider receiving from him a High Commissioner authorized to treat upon
                    the state of affairs and clothed with full power, or, if not convenient to
                    receive such a Commissioner personally, that each appoint such a High
                    Commissioner for the purpose named.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
